pear on the roster.\nIdea: Even adding the 2nd student should be done by invite. As long as the \"team\" doesn't have a 2nd student, it will not be a confirmed team (adding a state machine here?) and it will not appear in the list of teams on the website.\nOnce the 2nd student accepts the invitation, the teams gets confirmed and is officially created.", "body": "Non-orga people can no longer add mentors to their teams.\n\nCoaches added to the team will get an invite notification they can accept. Only then will they appear on the roster.\n\nIdea: Even adding the 2nd student should be done by invite. As long as the \"team\" doesn't have a 2nd student, it will not be a `confirmed` team (adding a state machine here?) and it will not appear in the list of teams on the website.\n\nOnce the 2nd student accepts the invitation, the teams gets confirmed and is officially created.\n"}